device.

00:11:30.806 --> 00:11:31.976 A:middle
And by the way, that's a great

00:11:31.976 --> 00:11:33.776 A:middle
tool for your toolbox to do

00:11:33.776 --> 00:11:34.866 A:middle
processing locally.

00:11:35.396 --> 00:11:39.196 A:middle
So to recap, three big ideas.

00:11:39.856 --> 00:11:43.706 A:middle
Privacy is about people, ask the

00:11:43.706 --> 00:11:46.386 A:middle
"should" questions, and align

00:11:46.386 --> 00:11:48.596 A:middle
your data practices with your

00:11:48.596 --> 00:11:49.496 A:middle
use cases.

00:11:51.256 --> 00:11:52.816 A:middle
In the time we have remaining, I

00:11:52.816 --> 00:11:53.996 A:middle
want to talk through some

00:11:53.996 --> 00:11:55.136 A:middle
features and tools that are

00:11:55.136 --> 00:11:56.856 A:middle
available to you as developers

00:11:56.856 --> 00:11:58.746 A:middle
to help you build privacy in

00:11:58.746 --> 00:12:00.046 A:middle
your app.


00:11:58.746 --> 00:12:00.046 A:middle
your app.

00:12:00.546 --> 00:12:02.216 A:middle
And these fall into two general

00:12:02.216 --> 00:12:03.866 A:middle
categories of accessing user

00:12:03.866 --> 00:12:05.986 A:middle
data and more broadly, data

00:12:05.986 --> 00:12:06.656 A:middle
stewardship.

00:12:07.896 --> 00:12:09.776 A:middle
So for data access, let's start

00:12:09.826 --> 00:12:12.336 A:middle
by talking about iOS, and much

00:12:12.336 --> 00:12:13.656 A:middle
of this guidance will apply to

00:12:13.656 --> 00:12:15.666 A:middle
tvOS and watchOS as well.

00:12:16.186 --> 00:12:18.576 A:middle
Let's imagine you're building a

00:12:18.576 --> 00:12:20.266 A:middle
game for iOS where players can

00:12:20.266 --> 00:12:21.916 A:middle
compete against each other, and

00:12:21.916 --> 00:12:22.746 A:middle
you want them to be able to

00:12:22.746 --> 00:12:24.256 A:middle
upload a photo to identify

00:12:24.256 --> 00:12:24.896 A:middle
themselves.

00:12:25.816 --> 00:12:26.716 A:middle
Now we've all seen those

00:12:26.756 --> 00:12:28.276 A:middle
permission prompts for access to

00:12:28.276 --> 00:12:30.386 A:middle
photos, but wouldn't it be great

00:12:30.386 --> 00:12:31.416 A:middle
if we could just have the user

00:12:31.416 --> 00:12:32.906 A:middle
click a button, select a

00:12:32.906 --> 00:12:34.436 A:middle
picture, and have it appear

00:12:34.436 --> 00:12:36.646 A:middle
immediately in their app?

00:12:37.276 --> 00:12:39.006 A:middle
Well, you can already do this

00:12:39.006 --> 00:12:39.396 A:middle
today.

00:12:40.786 --> 00:12:41.796 A:middle
Because we have a feature

00:12:41.796 --> 00:12:43.366 A:middle
available called out-of-process

00:12:43.366 --> 00:12:45.056 A:middle
pickers for contacts, camera,

00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:47.646 A:middle
and photos data, where the

00:12:47.646 --> 00:12:49.356 A:middle
picker that appears runs outside

00:12:49.356 --> 00:12:51.476 A:middle
your apps process so the only

00:12:51.476 --> 00:12:52.786 A:middle
information that's shared back

00:12:52.786 --> 00:12:54.396 A:middle
with the app is what the user

00:12:54.396 --> 00:12:55.096 A:middle
selects.

00:12:56.196 --> 00:12:57.916 A:middle
We talked about those privacy

00:12:57.916 --> 00:12:58.516 A:middle
techniques.

00:12:58.516 --> 00:13:00.256 A:middle
This is a case where because


00:12:58.516 --> 00:13:00.256 A:middle
This is a case where because

00:13:00.256 --> 00:13:01.856 A:middle
this doesn't involve ongoing

00:13:01.856 --> 00:13:03.846 A:middle
access to the entire library,

00:13:04.416 --> 00:13:06.376 A:middle
the user has control by picking

00:13:06.376 --> 00:13:08.266 A:middle
what they share, so we don't

00:13:08.266 --> 00:13:09.596 A:middle
need to show a permission prompt

00:13:09.916 --> 00:13:11.366 A:middle
and ask them to make a decision

00:13:11.556 --> 00:13:13.066 A:middle
about future access.

00:13:14.476 --> 00:13:16.976 A:middle
This is the default method for

00:13:16.976 --> 00:13:18.696 A:middle
accessing contacts, camera, and

00:13:18.696 --> 00:13:19.586 A:middle
photos data.

00:13:20.856 --> 00:13:22.176 A:middle
There are going to be times

00:13:22.176 --> 00:13:23.446 A:middle
where you may need access to the

00:13:23.446 --> 00:13:24.706 A:middle
broader library, but in most

00:13:24.706 --> 00:13:26.296 A:middle
situations, you'll find that

00:13:26.296 --> 00:13:27.936 A:middle
this works great for a whole lot

00:13:27.936 --> 00:13:29.186 A:middle
of apps.

00:13:31.876 --> 00:13:33.356 A:middle
This is a case where it does

00:13:33.356 --> 00:13:34.776 A:middle
just work and only requires a

00:13:34.776 --> 00:13:35.816 A:middle
few lines of code.

00:13:36.206 --> 00:13:37.326 A:middle
You can see some snippets here

00:13:37.326 --> 00:13:39.116 A:middle
for how to call these pickers in

00:13:39.116 --> 00:13:39.796 A:middle
your app.

00:13:40.656 --> 00:13:42.076 A:middle
Now as I said, there are going

00:13:42.076 --> 00:13:43.176 A:middle
to be some times where you do

00:13:43.176 --> 00:13:44.766 A:middle
need access to the broader data,

00:13:44.856 --> 00:13:46.026 A:middle
and as you know, there's a

00:13:46.026 --> 00:13:47.726 A:middle
variety of protected resources

00:13:47.726 --> 00:13:50.686 A:middle
available on the device, but if

00:13:50.686 --> 00:13:52.426 A:middle
you're using one of these APIs,

00:13:53.176 --> 00:13:54.256 A:middle
you need to keep in mind three

00:13:54.256 --> 00:13:55.336 A:middle
things before you start

00:13:55.336 --> 00:13:56.646 A:middle
requesting access.

00:13:57.986 --> 00:13:59.646 A:middle
You should only request access


00:14:00.226 --> 00:14:01.836 A:middle
to the data that's necessary for

00:14:01.836 --> 00:14:04.326 A:middle
your use case in your app.

00:14:05.056 --> 00:14:06.556 A:middle
If you don't actually need the

00:14:06.556 --> 00:14:08.716 A:middle
entire library of information,

00:14:09.496 --> 00:14:10.586 A:middle
rather than requesting it, you

00:14:10.586 --> 00:14:11.806 A:middle
should look for an alternative

00:14:11.806 --> 00:14:12.886 A:middle
solution, like those

00:14:12.886 --> 00:14:13.946 A:middle
out-of-process pickers.

00:14:15.096 --> 00:14:16.296 A:middle
You should only make these

00:14:16.296 --> 00:14:17.526 A:middle
requests when it's needed.

00:14:17.526 --> 00:14:19.556 A:middle
You want it to be in the moment

00:14:19.656 --> 00:14:21.936 A:middle
when a user makes a decision not

00:14:22.366 --> 00:14:23.636 A:middle
when they first open the app and

00:14:23.636 --> 00:14:25.126 A:middle
they're bombarded with questions

00:14:25.126 --> 00:14:26.586 A:middle
that they don't even understand

00:14:26.586 --> 00:14:26.886 A:middle
yet.

00:14:27.886 --> 00:14:29.016 A:middle
You want the prompt to be in

00:14:29.016 --> 00:14:29.876 A:middle
context.

00:14:30.606 --> 00:14:32.356 A:middle
But also you want to rely only

00:14:32.356 --> 00:14:33.946 A:middle
on the API for status.

00:14:34.956 --> 00:14:36.406 A:middle
Remember, a user can revoke

00:14:36.406 --> 00:14:38.046 A:middle
their decision at any time.

00:14:38.106 --> 00:14:39.546 A:middle
You just want make sure your app

00:14:39.546 --> 00:14:41.356 A:middle
still functions regardless of

00:14:41.356 --> 00:14:42.586 A:middle
what the user had decided.

00:14:44.326 --> 00:14:46.676 A:middle
Now when you request access, as

00:14:46.676 --> 00:14:47.996 A:middle
you know, you need to include a

00:14:47.996 --> 00:14:49.816 A:middle
purpose string or a usage

00:14:49.816 --> 00:14:50.366 A:middle
description.

00:14:51.446 --> 00:14:52.526 A:middle
And when I say you need to,

00:14:52.946 --> 00:14:54.466 A:middle
these are required.

00:14:55.596 --> 00:14:57.196 A:middle
You'll find your app rejected in

00:14:57.196 --> 00:14:58.406 A:middle
app review without these, and in

00:14:58.406 --> 00:14:59.716 A:middle
fact, you'll find your apps

00:14:59.716 --> 00:15:00.946 A:middle
start crashing if you try to


00:14:59.716 --> 00:15:00.946 A:middle
start crashing if you try to

00:15:00.946 --> 00:15:02.306 A:middle
access this data without a

00:15:02.306 --> 00:15:02.916 A:middle
purpose string.

00:15:04.356 --> 00:15:06.216 A:middle
Now this is one way of providing

00:15:06.216 --> 00:15:07.306 A:middle
transparency to users.

00:15:07.306 --> 00:15:08.686 A:middle
It's certainly not the only way.

00:15:09.546 --> 00:15:10.746 A:middle
By that, I don't mean showing a

00:15:10.746 --> 00:15:12.256 A:middle
fig prompt before the real one

00:15:12.256 --> 00:15:13.156 A:middle
to get them to click.

00:15:13.816 --> 00:15:14.596 A:middle
I mean this should be part of

00:15:14.596 --> 00:15:16.236 A:middle
the overall program of informing

00:15:16.236 --> 00:15:17.796 A:middle
your users about data flows in

00:15:17.796 --> 00:15:18.846 A:middle
your app.

00:15:19.496 --> 00:15:21.876 A:middle
The goal here is to explain the

00:15:21.876 --> 00:15:24.906 A:middle
reason for a request so that a

00:15:24.906 --> 00:15:26.526 A:middle
user can make an informed,

00:15:26.526 --> 00:15:28.716 A:middle
effective decision based on

00:15:28.716 --> 00:15:29.716 A:middle
their priorities.

00:15:30.226 --> 00:15:32.946 A:middle
When I say explain the reason,

00:15:33.676 --> 00:15:35.176 A:middle
this is not what I'm talking

00:15:35.176 --> 00:15:35.546 A:middle
about.

00:15:36.566 --> 00:15:37.996 A:middle
And we've seen purpose strings

00:15:37.996 --> 00:15:38.936 A:middle
like this in the past, but

00:15:38.936 --> 00:15:40.526 A:middle
again, this is going to lead to

00:15:40.526 --> 00:15:41.996 A:middle
rejections in app review.

00:15:43.246 --> 00:15:44.876 A:middle
We're increasingly enforcing

00:15:45.156 --> 00:15:47.086 A:middle
quality purpose strings both

00:15:47.086 --> 00:15:48.596 A:middle
through automated validation and

00:15:48.596 --> 00:15:49.396 A:middle
manual review.

00:15:50.766 --> 00:15:53.026 A:middle
Placeholders or blank strings

00:15:53.026 --> 00:15:54.286 A:middle
are not going to be sufficient.

00:15:54.676 --> 00:15:56.316 A:middle
Just saying advertising doesn't

00:15:56.316 --> 00:15:57.016 A:middle
tell a user much.

00:15:57.056 --> 00:15:58.796 A:middle
Requires location doesn't

00:15:58.796 --> 00:15:59.696 A:middle
explain the why.


