00:21:23.316 --> 00:21:23.826 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thanks Joey.

00:21:25.376 --> 00:21:27.046 A:middle
The web is one of the largest

00:21:27.046 --> 00:21:28.996 A:middle
venues for data access today.

00:21:29.856 --> 00:21:31.546 A:middle
If your business depends on

00:21:31.546 --> 00:21:33.286 A:middle
providing content on third-party

00:21:33.286 --> 00:21:35.226 A:middle
websites, this section is for

00:21:35.226 --> 00:21:35.406 A:middle
you.

00:21:37.336 --> 00:21:38.886 A:middle
This year we introduced the

00:21:38.886 --> 00:21:40.186 A:middle
Storage Access API.

00:21:41.106 --> 00:21:43.086 A:middle
The Storage Access API allows

00:21:43.086 --> 00:21:45.146 A:middle
users to engage with logged-in

00:21:45.146 --> 00:21:47.186 A:middle
content from embedded third

00:21:47.186 --> 00:21:49.926 A:middle
parties across the web including

00:21:50.126 --> 00:21:51.226 A:middle
from domains that have been

00:21:51.226 --> 00:21:53.236 A:middle
classified as a tracker by

00:21:53.236 --> 00:21:54.676 A:middle
intelligent tracking prevention.

00:21:55.806 --> 00:21:57.556 A:middle
Now the Storage Access API does

00:21:57.616 --> 00:21:59.386 A:middle
this only with the user's

00:21:59.426 --> 00:22:00.486 A:middle
explicit consent.


00:21:59.426 --> 00:22:00.486 A:middle
explicit consent.

00:22:01.016 --> 00:22:02.646 A:middle
Let's go through an example.

00:22:03.156 --> 00:22:05.696 A:middle
Here the user is browsing a news

00:22:05.696 --> 00:22:08.576 A:middle
site, news.example, and the news

00:22:08.576 --> 00:22:10.036 A:middle
site has an embedded video

00:22:10.036 --> 00:22:11.786 A:middle
player from video.example.

00:22:12.686 --> 00:22:14.676 A:middle
Now the user has a paid account

00:22:14.676 --> 00:22:16.406 A:middle
on the video site and would like

00:22:16.406 --> 00:22:17.986 A:middle
to grant the embedded video

00:22:17.986 --> 00:22:20.666 A:middle
access to its cookies so that

00:22:20.666 --> 00:22:22.226 A:middle
they can enjoy the benefits of

00:22:22.226 --> 00:22:24.066 A:middle
their subscription while reading

00:22:24.066 --> 00:22:24.566 A:middle
the news.

00:22:25.746 --> 00:22:26.676 A:middle
To accomplish this,

00:22:26.776 --> 00:22:29.146 A:middle
video.example needs to implement

00:22:29.206 --> 00:22:30.576 A:middle
the Storage Access API.

00:22:32.866 --> 00:22:35.356 A:middle
Video.example should add a call

00:22:35.446 --> 00:22:37.636 A:middle
to the Storage Access API when

00:22:37.636 --> 00:22:39.336 A:middle
the user clicks the play button

00:22:39.366 --> 00:22:40.486 A:middle
in their app.

00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:42.976 A:middle
Now this is an asynchronous API

00:22:43.086 --> 00:22:44.976 A:middle
that will return a promise, so

00:22:44.976 --> 00:22:46.206 A:middle
you should be prepared to handle

00:22:46.206 --> 00:22:47.856 A:middle
successes as well as failures.

00:22:48.396 --> 00:22:50.946 A:middle
So when a user clicks the play

00:22:50.946 --> 00:22:52.286 A:middle
button, this will kick off a

00:22:52.286 --> 00:22:54.726 A:middle
request, which will result in a

00:22:54.876 --> 00:22:57.296 A:middle
prompt asking the user if they

00:22:57.296 --> 00:22:58.146 A:middle
would like to grant

00:22:58.496 --> 00:23:00.776 A:middle
video.example access to its


00:22:58.496 --> 00:23:00.776 A:middle
video.example access to its

00:23:00.776 --> 00:23:02.676 A:middle
cookies while embedded in

00:23:02.676 --> 00:23:03.486 A:middle
news.example.

00:23:04.036 --> 00:23:06.896 A:middle
If the user clicks allow, this

00:23:06.896 --> 00:23:07.916 A:middle
choice will be sticky, and the

00:23:07.916 --> 00:23:09.566 A:middle
user won't be prompted again on

00:23:09.566 --> 00:23:11.006 A:middle
this combination of domains.

00:23:12.156 --> 00:23:13.516 A:middle
But if the user clicks deny, the

00:23:13.516 --> 00:23:14.776 A:middle
site can always reprompt.

00:23:15.186 --> 00:23:17.446 A:middle
Let's assume the user clicked

00:23:17.446 --> 00:23:17.836 A:middle
allow.

00:23:18.766 --> 00:23:20.776 A:middle
The request will go through, and

00:23:20.776 --> 00:23:22.396 A:middle
cookies will be returned to the

00:23:22.396 --> 00:23:22.996 A:middle
embedded site.

00:23:24.496 --> 00:23:25.376 A:middle
Now, this could create a

00:23:25.376 --> 00:23:27.106 A:middle
tracking risk as now

00:23:27.106 --> 00:23:29.466 A:middle
video.example has their users

00:23:29.566 --> 00:23:31.956 A:middle
logged in identity associated

00:23:31.956 --> 00:23:33.796 A:middle
with their presence on this news

00:23:33.796 --> 00:23:34.026 A:middle
site.

00:23:35.446 --> 00:23:36.926 A:middle
Now this is especially important

00:23:37.016 --> 00:23:38.616 A:middle
given changes to intelligent

00:23:38.616 --> 00:23:40.046 A:middle
tracking prevention this year.

00:23:41.016 --> 00:23:44.076 A:middle
Now outside of the user consent

00:23:44.076 --> 00:23:45.516 A:middle
provided via the Storage Access

00:23:45.516 --> 00:23:48.106 A:middle
API, cookies from domains that

00:23:48.106 --> 00:23:49.616 A:middle
are classified as trackers will

00:23:49.616 --> 00:23:52.156 A:middle
be partitioned immediately and

00:23:52.156 --> 00:23:53.316 A:middle
can never be used in a

00:23:53.316 --> 00:23:54.526 A:middle
third-party context.

00:23:55.916 --> 00:23:58.106 A:middle
Additionally, after 30 days

00:23:58.106 --> 00:23:59.566 A:middle
without user involvement, these

00:23:59.566 --> 00:24:01.236 A:middle
cookies will be purged entirely.


00:23:59.566 --> 00:24:01.236 A:middle
cookies will be purged entirely.

00:24:01.746 --> 00:24:05.346 A:middle
Now importantly here, access via

00:24:05.346 --> 00:24:07.466 A:middle
the Storage Access API will

00:24:07.466 --> 00:24:09.296 A:middle
count towards this 30-day

00:24:09.296 --> 00:24:10.176 A:middle
interaction timer.

00:24:11.196 --> 00:24:12.316 A:middle
That means that users who

00:24:12.346 --> 00:24:13.626 A:middle
interact frequently with your

00:24:13.626 --> 00:24:15.786 A:middle
site in a third-party context

00:24:16.016 --> 00:24:17.026 A:middle
will stay logged in.

00:24:17.476 --> 00:24:20.576 A:middle
So in this sequence, the user

00:24:20.776 --> 00:24:23.166 A:middle
will visit video.example both in

00:24:23.166 --> 00:24:24.956 A:middle
a first-party context, logged

00:24:24.956 --> 00:24:26.806 A:middle
into the home page, and in a

00:24:26.806 --> 00:24:28.456 A:middle
third-party context, where it's

00:24:28.456 --> 00:24:30.206 A:middle
embedded across the web.

00:24:31.056 --> 00:24:32.946 A:middle
So first, the user visits the

00:24:32.946 --> 00:24:34.736 A:middle
site in a first-party context.

00:24:35.606 --> 00:24:37.416 A:middle
Now notice that the days since

00:24:37.416 --> 00:24:39.206 A:middle
interaction timer will read zero

00:24:39.296 --> 00:24:40.856 A:middle
as the user is currently

00:24:40.856 --> 00:24:41.796 A:middle
interacting with the site.

00:24:43.476 --> 00:24:45.566 A:middle
But as the user interacts with

00:24:45.566 --> 00:24:47.166 A:middle
the embedded content throughout

00:24:47.166 --> 00:24:50.406 A:middle
their web browsing, the timer

00:24:50.406 --> 00:24:51.046 A:middle
will update.

00:24:52.466 --> 00:24:53.886 A:middle
This means that when the user

00:24:53.886 --> 00:24:56.146 A:middle
returns in a first-party

00:24:56.146 --> 00:24:58.316 A:middle
context, the days since

00:24:58.316 --> 00:25:00.426 A:middle
interaction timer will read 5


00:24:58.316 --> 00:25:00.426 A:middle
interaction timer will read 5

00:25:00.426 --> 00:25:04.026 A:middle
days despite there being 45 days

00:25:04.726 --> 00:25:06.136 A:middle
since the user was last on

00:25:06.136 --> 00:25:07.976 A:middle
video.example in a first-party

00:25:07.976 --> 00:25:08.686 A:middle
context.

00:25:10.096 --> 00:25:11.926 A:middle
Adopting the Storage Access API

00:25:11.926 --> 00:25:13.876 A:middle
will allow your users to stay

00:25:13.876 --> 00:25:16.446 A:middle
logged in and prevent unwanted

00:25:16.446 --> 00:25:16.816 A:middle
tracking.

00:25:17.306 --> 00:25:21.366 A:middle
Now privacy does not end with

00:25:21.366 --> 00:25:23.006 A:middle
gaining access to a user's data.

00:25:23.986 --> 00:25:25.336 A:middle
Privacy is a continued

00:25:25.336 --> 00:25:27.256 A:middle
obligation to your users to

00:25:27.256 --> 00:25:29.246 A:middle
maintain their trust throughout

00:25:29.246 --> 00:25:30.146 A:middle
the data's lifetime.

00:25:31.046 --> 00:25:32.636 A:middle
This is where data stewardship

00:25:32.766 --> 00:25:33.266 A:middle
begins.

00:25:33.866 --> 00:25:36.646 A:middle
Now I want to give you examples

00:25:36.646 --> 00:25:38.206 A:middle
from four areas of data

00:25:38.206 --> 00:25:39.466 A:middle
stewardship for you to think

00:25:39.466 --> 00:25:42.476 A:middle
about when developing your apps.

00:25:42.546 --> 00:25:43.406 A:middle
First is deletion.

00:25:44.356 --> 00:25:45.706 A:middle
Part of being a good data

00:25:45.706 --> 00:25:47.176 A:middle
steward is respecting your

00:25:47.176 --> 00:25:49.106 A:middle
user's intent to delete

00:25:49.106 --> 00:25:51.166 A:middle
something from your app.

00:25:52.696 --> 00:25:54.476 A:middle
So you should recognize that

00:25:54.476 --> 00:25:55.756 A:middle
there are data flows that go

00:25:55.846 --> 00:25:58.066 A:middle
outside your app, and you should

00:25:58.066 --> 00:26:00.236 A:middle
ensure consistency between these


00:25:58.066 --> 00:26:00.236 A:middle
ensure consistency between these

00:26:00.236 --> 00:26:02.136 A:middle
systems when the user deletes

00:26:02.136 --> 00:26:03.686 A:middle
something in your app.

00:26:04.346 --> 00:26:06.686 A:middle
Now the operating system doesn't

00:26:06.686 --> 00:26:08.066 A:middle
know what's happening inside

00:26:08.066 --> 00:26:09.776 A:middle
your app, so if you've donated

00:26:09.776 --> 00:26:11.586 A:middle
information to Siri Shortcuts or

00:26:11.586 --> 00:26:13.666 A:middle
posted a notification, you

00:26:13.666 --> 00:26:14.966 A:middle
should make sure that you delete

00:26:14.996 --> 00:26:16.786 A:middle
that content when the user

00:26:16.786 --> 00:26:18.486 A:middle
removes it from your app.

00:26:20.516 --> 00:26:22.936 A:middle
For example, if a user deletes

00:26:22.936 --> 00:26:25.186 A:middle
someone in your app's contact

00:26:25.186 --> 00:26:27.166 A:middle
list, Siri Suggestions should

00:26:27.166 --> 00:26:28.686 A:middle
not suggest them to message

00:26:28.686 --> 00:26:30.646 A:middle
using your app.

00:26:30.786 --> 00:26:32.826 A:middle
Or if a user deletes a thread in

00:26:32.826 --> 00:26:34.756 A:middle
your messaging application, you

00:26:34.756 --> 00:26:36.166 A:middle
should delete the notifications

00:26:36.166 --> 00:26:37.836 A:middle
for that content as well as it

00:26:37.836 --> 00:26:39.476 A:middle
would be unexpected for a user

00:26:39.476 --> 00:26:40.906 A:middle
to see notifications still on

00:26:40.906 --> 00:26:42.556 A:middle
their device from a thread they

00:26:42.556 --> 00:26:43.436 A:middle
thought they'd completely

00:26:43.436 --> 00:26:43.806 A:middle
deleted.

00:26:44.316 --> 00:26:46.696 A:middle
And finally, if you're a

00:26:46.696 --> 00:26:48.316 A:middle
passwords manager, and you've

00:26:48.316 --> 00:26:50.216 A:middle
donated passwords to the New

00:26:50.216 --> 00:26:52.346 A:middle
System Passwords API, you should

00:26:52.346 --> 00:26:53.326 A:middle
make sure to delete this

00:26:53.326 --> 00:26:55.336 A:middle
information if the user removes

